<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-24T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-24T14:00:00-05:00" n="244" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d244">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">714.44A15/242: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Des Portes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-24T13:00:00-06:00">May 24, 1941—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 3:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>71. My telegram no. 70, May 23, 1 p.m. The Chief of Protocol has just
                            called at the Legation with a message from President Ubico in which the
                            President confirms the Foreign Minister’s statement.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Des Portes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>